	<h1>Len Lye</h1>

	<h2>About</h2>

		<p>Leonard Charles Huia "Len" Lye (5 July 1901 - 15 May 1980), was a Christchurch, New Zealand-born artist known primarily for his experimental films and kinetic sculpture.</p>

		<p><strong>Born</strong>Leonard Charles Huia Lye<br>June 5, 1901<br>Christchurch,South Island,New Zealand<br><strong>Died</strong>May 15,1980 (aged 78)<br>Warwick, New York, United States<br><strong>Nationality</strong>New Zealander, American<br><strong>Known</strong>for Film, sculpture</p>

